This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of motion blur in videos captured by hand-held devices. The use of deep learning techniques to solve this problem also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.MM) and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves aligning images, which could place it in the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of high-level scene understanding to identify accurately aligned regions could suggest that it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
